NATO air raids on Yugoslavia should be stopped
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the central committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, issued a statement to the press on May 14 in connection with escalating U.S.-led NATO air raids on Yugoslavia.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The U.S.-led NATO attack on Yugoslavia is an extreme arbitrariness  violating the UN Charter and the recognized principle of the international law, the statement said, and went on:   The U.S.-led NATO forces  struck and destroyed a number of factories, enterprises, schools, hospitals, kindergartens and even running buses, not military objects, and  bombed even the Chinese embassy,  and tried to defend themselves by saying "it is possible damage" and "mistake."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   All the facts clearly prove that "human rights", "humanitarianism" and "peace" on the lips of organizers of aggression and accomplices are a mask to cover up their arbitrary acts to dominate the world.
   The more the U.S.-led NATO forces escalate their aggression, the deeper they will be driven into dilemma and the bitterer their political, moral and military defeat will be.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Korean working class and other people express firm support and solidarity for the just struggle of the Yugoslav working class and other people to defend the dignity and sovereignty of the country.
   We strongly urge the aggressors to clearly see the situation, lend an ear to unanimous denunciation by the Yugoslav people and peace-loving people of the world and stop the unlawful attack at once.

S. Korean worker's struggle supported
 Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today carries a signed commentary on the second general strike South Korean workers have started with a strike of the Federation of Hospital Workers Unions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The news analyst says:   The South Korean Confederation of Trade Unions strongly urged the authorities to stop the layoff and reduce working hours with the beginning of the second general strike, and the strike is expected to spread all over the country.
   The second general strike of South Korean workers is an eruption of pent-up hatred and resentment against the ruling quarters, stemming from their will to live a life worthy of humanity.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They drew lessons from their strike again that they should not  have the slightest illusion about the ruling quarters and "dialogue and negotiation" on their lips are no more than appeasement and deception merely to put down resentment of workers.
  This struggle resumed on the occasion of the anniversary of the May 18 Kwangju Uprising shows that their struggle will be strengthened as long as the colonial fascist rule of the U.S. and the treacherous misrule of the authorities are sustained in South Korea.

Prelude to war
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Recently the U.S. war hawks are resorting to arms buildup and keeping war posture, alleging that "military vacuum" in South Korea was caused by the Yugoslav crisis and "emergencies" May be created by someone.
   Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun today says:   Their remarks are a pretext to justify the moves for another war of aggression on Korea and bring a second Yugoslav crisis to the Korean peninsula.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Regarding the peninsula as a vantage for realizing its ambition for domination over Asia, the United States has set it as a primary target of its reactionary Asia strategy  and the main task for strategic predominance in this region to ignite a second Korean war and seize the peninsula. 
   The U.S. Defense Secretary said the U.S. forces are prepared for three limited wars, which means to unleash another war on the Korean peninsula along with the attack on Yugoslavia.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Now that the United States is attempting to unleash a second war of aggression on Korea on the plea of the Yugoslav crisis, the DPRK cannot but keep full readiness and sharply watch  every U.S. movement.

U.S. ambition for hegemonistic domination
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Minju Joson in a commentary today denounces the United States for scheming to establish the "Theatre Missile Defense" system (TMD) in east Asia in a bid to realize its ambition for world supremacy.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Some time ago, the U.S. Defense Department submitted to the congress a report on establishing the TMD system in Japan, South Korea and other areas of east Asia on the pretext of "coping with possible 'missile attack' by North Korea," and the congress urged the establishment of "joint early warning system" among the U.S., Japan and South Korea on the same pretext.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The news analyst of the paper says:   This openly revealed the U.S. ambition for hegemonistic domination over east Asia.
   The TMD plan is aimed at ensuring the U.S. military supremacy over any regions of the world on the signboard of "defense" following the changed reality and at dominating these regions and the rest of the world by relying on it.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is the U.S. strategy to take hold on east Asia, establish the sphere of domination over the Asia-Pacific region with it as a springboard and, moreover, dominate the world.
   It is as clear as noonday that military balance in east Asia will be  seriously destroyed and a new arms race and cold war be caused by the U.S. moves to establish the TMD system in the region.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The moves, contrary to the trend of the times toward peace and detente, can never be justified.

Achievements in geological prospecting 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, May 15 (KCNA) -- Geological prospecting workers have worked out a detailed topographical map for geological prospecting of the country before finding various mineral resources and prospecting promising areas to be developed.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Despite hard conditions, geological prospecting workers and officials climbed hundreds of steep mountains and introduced new methods in surveying to make a more detailed and correct topographical map.    With this map they ensured the scientific accuracy of all prospecting and increased prospecting efficiency so as to comprehensively develop and utilize underground resources and land for the building of a powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Geological prospectors in south Phyongan, south Hamgyong and north Hwanghae provinces increased the estimated amount of coal deposits of coal mines and found more areas to develop new coal mines by prospecting new areas. 
   Prospecting teams under the Jagang Provincial Prospecting Management Bureau have found more coal resources with a view to operating local industrial factories and improving the standard of people's living.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Surveying teams in south Phyongan and other provinces found a lot of mineral resources of fertilizers for agricultural production.
   The western area iron prospecting corps secured the foundations to develop new iron ore mines.
   Geological prospectors in north Phyongan and north and south Hwanghae provinces discovered promising and high-grade nonferrous minerals and more deposits of ore mines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Geological prospectors found mineral resources of different kinds including alloy element needed to develop ultra-modern science and technology.
